---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import UTCGMTConverter from '../components/UTCGMTConverter.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="UTC/GMT Converter — Convert to and from UTC | Clockr"
	description="Convert any local time to UTC/GMT or UTC back to your time zone. Free UTC converter with automatic daylight saving adjustment."
	category="timezones"
>
	<div class="ugc-page">
		<div class="ugc-header">
			<div class="ugc-eyebrow">
				<span class="ugc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				Time Zones
			</div>
			<h1 class="ugc-title">
				<span class="ugc-gradient">UTC/GMT</span><br />
				<span class="ugc-gradient">Converter</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="ugc-subtitle">
				Convert any time to or from UTC/GMT instantly
			</p>
		</div>

		<UTCGMTConverter client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="ugc-how">
			<h2 class="ugc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="ugc-how-card">
				<p>
					UTC (Coordinated Universal Time) is the global reference clock that
					every time zone is measured against. It replaced GMT as the
					international standard in 1972 and is kept precise using atomic
					clocks. Airlines, military operations, scientific research, and
					computer servers all rely on UTC so that events can be coordinated
					across borders without ambiguity.
				</p>
				<p>
					UTC and GMT are closely related but not identical in strict terms. UTC
					is the modern time standard maintained by atomic clocks, while GMT is
					technically a time zone centred on Greenwich, London. In everyday use
					the two names are interchangeable — both represent offset zero — but
					UTC is the correct term for the global reference. This converter
					displays results as UTC/GMT to reflect that common usage.
				</p>
				<p>
					Daylight saving time shifts local clocks forward or back by an hour in
					many countries, which changes the offset between a city and UTC
					throughout the year. London is UTC+0 in winter (GMT) but UTC+1 in
					summer (BST); New York is UTC−5 in winter and UTC−4 in summer. Clockr
					uses IANA timezone data through the browser's Intl API, so the
					correct offset for your chosen date is applied automatically — no
					manual adjustment needed.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="ugc-faq">
			<h2 class="ugc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="ugc-faq-list">
				<details class="ugc-faq-item">
					<summary class="ugc-faq-question"
						>What is UTC and how is it different from GMT?</summary
					>
					<div class="ugc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							UTC (Coordinated Universal Time) is the world's primary time
							standard, maintained by atomic clocks and accurate to within a
							fraction of a second. GMT (Greenwich Mean Time) is a time zone
							based on the sun's position at the Royal Observatory in Greenwich,
							London. In practice the two are used interchangeably for offset
							zero, but UTC is the technically correct term for the global
							reference.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ugc-faq-item">
					<summary class="ugc-faq-question"
						>What is the current UTC offset for London?</summary
					>
					<div class="ugc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							London is UTC+0 during winter when GMT is in effect, and UTC+1
							during summer when British Summer Time (BST) is active. The switch
							happens on the last Sunday in March (clocks forward) and the last
							Sunday in October (clocks back). Use the converter above with
							London selected to see the live offset for today's date.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ugc-faq-item">
					<summary class="ugc-faq-question"
						>How do I convert UTC to my local time?</summary
					>
					<div class="ugc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Enter the UTC time and date in the "UTC to your time" card, then
							select your city from the time zone dropdown. The converter
							instantly shows the equivalent local time and date, accounting
							for daylight saving on that specific day. Your browser's time zone
							is detected automatically as the default.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ugc-faq-item">
					<summary class="ugc-faq-question"
						>Why do clocks change between GMT and BST?</summary
					>
					<div class="ugc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The UK observes daylight saving time to make better use of evening
							daylight during the longer summer days. Clocks spring forward one
							hour to BST in late March and fall back to GMT in late October.
							This shifts the offset from UTC+0 to UTC+1 for roughly seven months
							of the year.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ugc-faq-item">
					<summary class="ugc-faq-question"
						>Is UTC the same as Greenwich Mean Time?</summary
					>
					<div class="ugc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							For most practical purposes, yes — both represent the same offset
							(zero) and are used interchangeably in aviation, broadcasting,
							and computing. Strictly speaking, UTC is an atomic time standard
							while GMT is a solar-based time zone, but the difference is less
							than a second and irrelevant for everyday conversions.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ugc-faq-item">
					<summary class="ugc-faq-question"
						>What time zone do pilots and the military use?</summary
					>
					<div class="ugc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Aviation and military operations worldwide use UTC (often called
							"Zulu time" in aviation). Flight plans, air traffic control
							clearances, and military orders are all expressed in UTC to avoid
							confusion across time zones. NATO and many armed forces also use
							the NATO phonetic alphabet, where Zulu represents UTC.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ugc-faq-item">
					<summary class="ugc-faq-question"
						>How is UTC time used in computing and servers?</summary
					>
					<div class="ugc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Computer systems store and process timestamps in UTC internally,
							then convert to local time only when displaying to users. Unix
							timestamps, database records, log files, and API responses all use
							UTC to ensure consistency across servers in different regions.
							Converting UTC to local time is one of the most common tasks in
							software development.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="ugc-related">
			<h3 class="ugc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="ugc-related-grid">
				<a href="/world-clock" class="ugc-related-card"
					><span class="ugc-related-name">World Clock</span></a
				>
				<a href="/timezone-converter" class="ugc-related-card"
					><span class="ugc-related-name">Time Zone Converter</span></a
				>
				<a href="/time-zone-meeting-planner" class="ugc-related-card"
					><span class="ugc-related-name">Time Zone Meeting Planner</span></a
				>
				<a href="/time-difference" class="ugc-related-card"
					><span class="ugc-related-name">Time Difference Calculator</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.ugc-page {
		max-width: 1100px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.ugc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.ugc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.ugc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.ugc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.ugc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.ugc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.ugc-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 24px;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.ugc-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 28px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.06);
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 20px;
	}

	.ugc-card-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.ugc-time-row {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-end;
		gap: 8px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.ugc-time-input-wrap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
		flex: 1;
		min-width: 72px;
	}

	.ugc-time-sep {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		padding-bottom: 12px;
		line-height: 1;
	}

	.ugc-time-input {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 12px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 28px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		width: 100%;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
		-moz-appearance: textfield;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
	}

	.ugc-time-input::-webkit-outer-spin-button,
	.ugc-time-input::-webkit-inner-spin-button {
		-webkit-appearance: none;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.ugc-time-input:focus {
		border-color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.15);
	}

	.ugc-period-toggle {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 4px;
		padding-bottom: 2px;
	}

	.ugc-period-btn {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.25);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 8px 12px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
	}

	.ugc-period-btn--active {
		background: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.12);
		border-color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.6);
		color: #00e5c4;
	}

	.ugc-period-btn:hover:not(.ugc-period-btn--active) {
		border-color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.4);
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
	}

	.ugc-field {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.ugc-field-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
	}

	.ugc-input,
	.ugc-select {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #ffffff;
		outline: none;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
		width: 100%;
	}

	.ugc-input:focus,
	.ugc-select:focus {
		border-color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.15);
	}

	.ugc-select option {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.ugc-offset {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		line-height: 1.5;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 12px 14px;
		background: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.04);
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.12);
		border-radius: 10px;
	}

	.ugc-output {
		background: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.04);
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.25);
		border-radius: 16px;
		padding: 28px 20px;
		text-align: center;
		margin-top: auto;
	}

	.ugc-output-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	.ugc-output-time {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 10px;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
	}

	.ugc-output-date {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
	}

	.ugc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.ugc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.ugc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.ugc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.ugc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.ugc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.ugc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.ugc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.ugc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.ugc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.ugc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.ugc-faq-item[open] .ugc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.ugc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.ugc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.ugc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.ugc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.ugc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.ugc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.ugc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(0, 229, 196, 0.4);
	}

	.ugc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00e5c4, #0099ff);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 767px) {
		.ugc-title {
			font-size: 48px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.ugc-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.ugc-card {
			padding: 24px 16px;
		}

		.ugc-output-time {
			font-size: 48px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.ugc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.ugc-time-input {
			font-size: 24px;
		}
	}
</style>
